This README file contains information on the contents of the
rhaberkorn Yocto layer.
This layer contains ports of programs under the Github account
https://github.com/rhaberkorn

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake
  branch: master

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta
  branch: master

and will also work with Yocto/Poky


Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the rhaberkorn layer to the
maintainer robin.haberkorn@googlemail.com.
Alternatively, create a Github pull request.


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the rhaberkorn layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the rhaberkorn layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the rhaberkorn layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the rhaberkorn layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-rhaberkorn \
    "


